780
00:51:07,944 --> 00:51:11,364
<i>Our forces rallied...

781
00:51:11,365 --> 00:51:15,034
<i>...and drove the Orcs back.

782
00:51:15,035 --> 00:51:17,161
<i>And our enemy...

783
00:51:17,162 --> 00:51:20,623
<i>...had been defeated.

784
00:51:20,624 --> 00:51:23,667
But there was no feast...

785
00:51:23,668 --> 00:51:26,629
...nor song that night...

786
00:51:26,630 --> 00:51:31,630
<i>...for our dead
were beyond the count of grief.

787
00:51:32,469 --> 00:51:37,469
<i>We few had survived.

788
00:51:42,979 --> 00:51:47,979
<i>And I thought to myself then...

789
00:51:48,652 --> 00:51:53,652
<i>...there is one who I could follow.

790
00:51:55,158 --> 00:51:58,035
There is one...

791
00:51:58,036 --> 00:52:03,036
...I could call king.

792
00:52:18,974 --> 00:52:22,685
And the pale Orc?

793
00:52:22,686 --> 00:52:24,353
What happened to him?

794
00:52:24,354 --> 00:52:28,315
He slunk back into the hole
whence he came.

795
00:52:28,316 --> 00:52:33,316
That filth died of his wounds long ago.

796
