02:28:03,004 --> 02:28:04,421
Come on, quickly!

2045
02:28:04,422 --> 02:28:09,422
- Come on, move!
- Bombur!

2046
02:28:12,763 --> 02:28:17,763
Go, go, go!

2047
02:28:18,311 --> 02:28:23,311
Jump!

2048
02:28:25,484 --> 02:28:30,484
Jump, lad!

2049
02:28:47,298 --> 02:28:50,926
Come on!

2050
02:28:50,927 --> 02:28:55,927
Push!

2051
02:29:11,197 --> 02:29:16,197
Come on!

2052
02:29:18,371 --> 02:29:23,371
Come on!

2053
02:29:25,878 --> 02:29:27,087
Watch your backs!

2054
02:29:27,088 --> 02:29:32,088
You thought you could escape me.

2055
02:29:33,261 --> 02:29:38,139
What are you going to do now, Wizard?

2056
02:29:44,188 --> 02:29:49,188
That'll do it.

2057
02:30:20,683 --> 02:30:23,852
Well, that could have been worse.

2058
02:30:23,853 --> 02:30:25,645
Haver!

2059
02:30:25,646 --> 02:30:30,646
You've got to be joking!

2060
02:30:34,155 --> 02:30:35,780
Gandalf!

2061
02:30:40,202 --> 02:30:42,620
There's too many. We can't fight them.

2062
02:30:42,621 --> 02:30:44,873
Only one thing will save us, daylight!

2063
02:30:44,874 --> 02:30:46,291
Come on!

2064
02:30:46,292 --> 02:30:50,378
Here! On your feet.

2065
02:30:50,379 --> 02:30:53,340
- Balin.
- Come on!

2066
02:30:54,425 --> 02:30:56,426
Wait!

2067
02:30:56,427 --> 02:30:59,679
My precious. Wait!

2068
02:30:59,680 --> 02:31:03,433
Gollum, gollum!

2069
02:31:07,438 --> 02:31:10,899
Quick, quick!

2070
02:31:10,900 --> 02:31:12,150
This way.

2071
02:31:14,695 --> 02:31:19,695
- Come on.
- Come on, come on. Quickly.

2072
02:31:20,451 --> 02:31:25,451
Right, good!

2073
02:32:49,206 --> 02:32:51,916
Baggins!

2074
02:32:51,917 --> 02:32:54,752
Thief!

2075
02:32:54,753 --> 02:32:59,753
Curse it and crush it!
We hates it forever!

2076
02:33:12,605 --> 02:33:15,523
Five, six, seven, eight.

2077
02:33:15,524 --> 02:33:17,984
Bifur. Bofur. That's 10.

2078
02:33:17,985 --> 02:33:20,778
Fili, Kili! That's 12.

2079
02:33:20,779 --> 02:33:24,699
And Bombur. That makes 13.

2080
02:33:24,700 --> 02:33:26,826
Where's Bilbo?

2081
02:33:26,827 --> 02:33:29,996
Where is our Hobbit?

2082
02:33:29,997 --> 02:33:33,041
Where is our Hobbit?

2083
02:33:33,042 --> 02:33:34,876
Curse that Halfling!

2084
02:33:34,877 --> 02:33:36,169
Now he's lost?

2085
02:33:36,170 --> 02:33:38,338
I thought he was with Dori!

2086
02:33:38,339 --> 02:33:39,589
Don't blame me!

2087
02:33:39,590 --> 02:33:40,924
Where did you last see him?

2088
02:33:40,925 --> 02:33:41,841
I think I saw him...

2089
02:33:41,842 --> 02:33:42,800
...slip away...

2090
02:33:42,801 --> 02:33:43,760
...when they first collared us.

2091
02:33:43,761 --> 02:33:45,386
And what happened, exactly?

2092
02:33:45,387 --> 02:33:47,889
- Tell me!
- I'll tell you what happened.

2093
02:33:47,890 --> 02:33:49,724
Master Baggins saw his chance...

2094
02:33:49,725 --> 02:33:51,518
...and he took it.

2095
02:33:51,519 --> 02:33:54,437
He has thought of nothing
but his soft bed and his warm hearth...

2096
02:33:54,438 --> 02:33:57,315
...since first he stepped out of his door.

2097
02:33:57,316 --> 02:34:00,276
We will not be seeing our Hobbit again.

2098
02:34:00,277 --> 02:34:05,277
He is long gone.

2099
02:34:14,041 --> 02:34:16,042
No.

2100
02:34:16,043 --> 02:34:21,005
He isn't.

2101
02:34:21,006 --> 02:34:22,840
Bilbo Baggins.

2102
02:34:22,841 --> 02:34:24,217
I have never been so glad...

2103
02:34:24,218 --> 02:34:27,804
...to see anyone in my life.

2104
02:34:27,805 --> 02:34:28,972
Bilbo.

2105
02:34:28,973 --> 02:34:29,931
We'd given you up.

2106
02:34:29,932 --> 02:34:32,100
How on earth
did you get past the Goblins?

2107
02:34:32,101 --> 02:34:37,021
How, indeed.

2108
02:34:42,820 --> 02:34:46,906
Well, what does it matter? He's back.

2109
02:34:46,907 --> 02:34:48,408
It matters.

2110
02:34:48,409 --> 02:34:51,953
I want to know.

2111
02:34:51,954 --> 02:34:56,954
Why did you come back?

2112
02:34:57,001 --> 02:35:02,001
Look, I know you doubt me.
I know you always have.

2113
02:35:02,298 --> 02:35:05,174
And you're right.
I often think of Bag-end.

2114
02:35:05,175 --> 02:35:07,969
I miss my books.

2115
02:35:07,970 --> 02:35:11,764
And my armchair and my garden.

2116
02:35:11,765 --> 02:35:13,808
See, that's where I belong.

2117
02:35:13,809 --> 02:35:17,270
That's home.

2118
02:35:17,271 --> 02:35:21,691
And that's why I came back. Because...

2119
02:35:21,692 --> 02:35:25,236
...you don't have one. A home.

2120
02:35:25,237 --> 02:35:29,907
It was taken from you.

2121
02:35:29,908 --> 02:35:34,908
But I will help you take it back if I can.

2122
02:35:55,351 --> 02:36:00,351
{\an8}<font color=#FF0000>Gorid dum! Ragshid shirzlum!
<font color=#FFFF00>(Run them down to the end. Tear them to pieces!)</font>

2123
02:36:05,944 --> 02:36:07,612
Out of the frying pan.

2124
02:36:07,613 --> 02:36:10,239
And into the fire. Run.

2125
02:36:10,240 --> 02:36:15,240
Run!

2126
02:36:27,383 --> 02:36:32,383
Go!

2127
02:36:55,953 --> 02:36:56,869
Up into the trees!

2128
02:36:56,870 --> 02:36:58,079
All of you!

2129
02:36:58,080 --> 02:37:00,039
Climb! Bilbo, climb!

2130
02:37:00,040 --> 02:37:05,040
Quickly!

2131
02:37:11,427 --> 02:37:16,427
They're coming!

2132
02:37:51,008 --> 02:37:53,259
- Hang on!
- Hold on, brothers!

2133
02:38:14,156 --> 02:38:15,990
Azog.

2134
02:38:21,580 --> 02:38:27,000
{\an8}<font color=#FF0000>Nuzdigid? Nuzdi gast?
<font color=#FFFF00>(Do you smell it? The scent of fear?)</font>

2135
02:38:31,200 --> 02:38:41,000
{\an8}<font color=#FF0000>Ganziliz i u narug obod nauzdanish... Torin undag Train.
<font color=#FFFF00>(I remembered your father reeked of it... Thorin son of Thrain.)</font>

2136
02:38:42,309 --> 02:38:47,309
It cannot be.

2137
02:38:49,600 --> 02:38:58,500
{\an8}<font color=#FF0000>Kod... toragid biriz... Worori-da!
<font color=#FFFF00>(Bring that one to me... Kill the others!)</font>

2138
02:39:23,700 --> 02:39:26,000
{\an8}<font color=#FF0000>Shog agradol!</font>
<font color=#FFFF00>(Drink their blood!)</font>

2139
02:39:37,614 --> 02:39:39,282
It's going!

2140
02:40:28,624 --> 02:40:33,624
Fili!

2141
02:40:54,483 --> 02:40:55,733
Yeah!

2142
02:41:04,743 --> 02:41:06,535
No!

2143
02:41:12,709 --> 02:41:17,709
Oh, no.

2144
02:41:18,966 --> 02:41:23,966
Mr. Gandalf!

2145
02:41:26,306 --> 02:41:29,100
Oh, no, Dori!

2146
02:42:38,295 --> 02:42:43,295
Help!

2147
02:42:57,689 --> 02:43:01,067
No!

2148
02:43:11,578 --> 02:43:16,578
Thorin! No!

2149
02:43:32,599 --> 02:43:37,599
{\an8}<font color=#FF0000>Biriz torag khobdudol!</font>
<font color=#FFFF00>(Bring me his head!)</font>

2150
02:44:25,500 --> 02:44:28,000
{\an8}<font color=#FF0000>{\an8}<font color=#FF0000>Gorid dum!</font>
<font color=#FFFF00>(Kill him!)</font>

2151
02:46:12,384 --> 02:46:14,093
Look.

2152
02:47:01,516 --> 02:47:06,516
Thorin!

2153
02:48:18,134 --> 02:48:23,134
Thorin!

2154
02:48:23,473 --> 02:48:28,473
Thorin.

2155
02:48:42,075 --> 02:48:44,243
The Halfling?

2156
02:48:44,244 --> 02:48:46,703
It's all right.

2157
02:48:46,704 --> 02:48:47,913
Bilbo is here.

2158
02:48:47,914 --> 02:48:50,124
He's quite safe.

2159
02:48:59,801 --> 02:49:04,801
You!

2160
02:49:04,806 --> 02:49:06,765
What were you doing?

2161
02:49:06,766 --> 02:49:07,808
You nearly got...

2162
02:49:07,809 --> 02:49:11,019
...yourself killed!

2163
02:49:11,020 --> 02:49:12,020
Did I not say...

2164
02:49:12,021 --> 02:49:14,773
...that you would be a burden?

2165
02:49:14,774 --> 02:49:18,402
That you would not survive in the Wild?

2166
02:49:18,403 --> 02:49:23,403
That you had no place amongst us?

2167
02:49:25,910 --> 02:49:30,910
I have never been so wrong in all my life.

2168
02:49:41,968 --> 02:49:43,760
I am sorry I doubted you.

2169
02:49:43,761 --> 02:49:46,805
No, I would have doubted me too.

2170
02:49:46,806 --> 02:49:48,056
I'm not a hero...

2171
02:49:48,057 --> 02:49:51,477
...or a warrior.

2172
02:49:51,478 --> 02:49:52,394
Not even...

2173
02:49:52,395 --> 02:49:57,395
...a burglar.

2174
02:50:13,082 --> 02:50:18,082
Is that what I think it is?

2175
02:50:30,558 --> 02:50:33,227
Erebor...

2176
02:50:33,228 --> 02:50:35,020
...the Lonely Mountain...

2177
02:50:35,021 --> 02:50:37,231
...the last of the great Dwarf kingdoms...

2178
02:50:37,232 --> 02:50:42,232
...of Middle-earth.

2179
02:50:42,403 --> 02:50:47,366
Our home.

2180
02:50:48,660 --> 02:50:50,244
A raven!

2181
02:50:50,245 --> 02:50:51,286
The birds...

2182
02:50:51,287 --> 02:50:56,287
...are returning to the mountain.

2183
02:50:56,709 --> 02:50:58,710
That, my dear Oin...

2184
02:50:58,711 --> 02:51:01,713
...is a thrush.

2185
02:51:01,714 --> 02:51:04,049
But we'll take it as a sign.

2186
02:51:04,050 --> 02:51:05,300
A good omen.

2187
02:51:05,301 --> 02:51:07,511
You're right.

2188
02:51:07,512 --> 02:51:12,512
I do believe the worst is behind us.

2189
02:53:03,211 --> 02:53:05,712
<i>Far over

2190
02:53:05,713 --> 02:53:10,713
<i>The misty mountains rise

2191
02:53:11,219 --> 02:53:14,971
<i>Leave us standing

2192
02:53:14,972 --> 02:53:19,017
<i>Upon the height

2193
02:53:19,018 --> 02:53:22,979
<i>What was before

2194
02:53:22,980 --> 02:53:27,109
<i>We see once more

2195
02:53:27,110 --> 02:53:32,110
<i>Is our kingdom a distant light

2196
02:53:34,367 --> 02:53:39,367
<i>Fiery mountain beneath the moon

2197
02:53:41,165 --> 02:53:45,127
<i>The words unspoken

2198
02:53:45,128 --> 02:53:49,297
<i>We'll be there soon

2199
02:53:49,298 --> 02:53:53,301
<i>For home a song

2200
02:53:53,302 --> 02:53:57,347
<i>That echoes on

2201
02:53:57,348 --> 02:54:02,348
<i>And all who find us will know the tune

2202
02:54:06,023 --> 02:54:10,026
<i>Some folk we never forget

2203
02:54:10,027 --> 02:54:14,197
<i>Some kind we never forgive

2204
02:54:14,198 --> 02:54:18,285
<i>Haven't seen the back of us yet

2205
02:54:18,286 --> 02:54:22,289
<i>We'll fight as long as we live

2206
02:54:22,290 --> 02:54:26,209
<i>All eyes on the hidden door

2207
02:54:26,210 --> 02:54:30,338
<i>To the Lonely Mountain borne

2208
02:54:30,339 --> 02:54:34,134
<i>We'll ride in the gathering storm

2209
02:54:34,135 --> 02:54:39,135
<i>Until we get our long-forgotten gold

2210
02:54:41,142 --> 02:54:43,518
<i>We lay under

2211
02:54:43,519 --> 02:54:48,519
<i>The misty mountains cold

2212
02:54:48,858 --> 02:54:52,527
<i>In slumbers deep

2213
02:54:52,528 --> 02:54:56,823
<i>And dreams of gold

2214
02:54:56,824 --> 02:55:00,911
<i>We must awake

2215
02:55:00,912 --> 02:55:04,915
<i>Our lives to make

2216
02:55:04,916 --> 02:55:09,916
<i>And in the darkness a torch we hold

2217
02:55:12,006 --> 02:55:17,006
<i>From long ago when lanterns burned

2218
02:55:19,013 --> 02:55:23,058
<i>Until this day

2219
02:55:23,059 --> 02:55:27,062
<i>Our hearts have yearned

2220
02:55:27,063 --> 02:55:31,191
<i>Her fate unknown

2221
02:55:31,192 --> 02:55:35,320
<i>The Arkenstone

2222
02:55:35,321 --> 02:55:39,157
<i>What was stolen

2223
02:55:39,158 --> 02:55:44,158
<i>Must be returned

2224
02:55:57,343 --> 02:56:01,304
<i>We must awake

2225
02:56:01,305 --> 02:56:05,350
<i>And make the day

2226
02:56:05,351 --> 02:56:09,187
<i>To find a song

2227
02:56:09,188 --> 02:56:14,188
<i>For heart and soul

2228
02:56:15,027 --> 02:56:19,072
<i>Some folk we never forget

2229
02:56:19,073 --> 02:56:23,243
<i>Some kind we never forgive

2230
02:56:23,244 --> 02:56:27,372
<i>Haven't seen the end of it yet

2231
02:56:27,373 --> 02:56:31,293
<i>We'll fight as long as we live

2232
02:56:31,294 --> 02:56:35,338
<i>All eyes on the hidden door

2233
02:56:35,339 --> 02:56:39,426
<i>To the Lonely Mountain borne

2234
02:56:39,427 --> 02:56:43,430
<i>We'll ride in the gathering storm

2235
02:56:43,431 --> 02:56:48,431
<i>Till we get our long-forgotten gold

2236
02:56:49,896 --> 02:56:52,564
<i>Far away

2237
02:56:52,565 --> 02:56:57,565
<i>From misty mountains cold
